
[1]slaughter

   SLAUGHTER, n. slaw'ter [See Slay.]

   1. In a general sense, a killing. Applied to men, slaughter usually
   denotes great destruction of life by violent means; as the slaughter of
   men in battle.

   2. Applied to beasts, butchery; a killing of oxen or other beasts for
   market.

                          SLAUGHTER, v.t. slaw'ter.

   1. To kill; to slay; to make great destruction of life; as , to
   slaughter men in battle.

   2. To butcher; to kill for the market; as beasts.
